inn1.comm: straight as a die, slightly back of a length, defended off the back foot
outside off stump, good carry again, left alone to the keeper
on the hip, turned down to fine leg, Australia are off the mark
attacking the top of off stump, back of a length again, defended urgently back down the pitch
blocked once again, a good tidy over so far to kick off the day's proceedings
nothing to work with there, slightly angled into the pads, but starting from an off stump line. Defended to midwicket
top strike! Only three on the leg-side, so Watson flicks gloriously, and no-one can stop the boundary through midwicket

Review! Watson was eyeing up those acres on the leg-side again. Playing all around his front pad, and Pakistan ask for a second opinion. Very full length, but probably missing leg. No idea why these reviews are taking so long at the moment. Just get us the pitch map. Sure enough, it's an umpire's call
speared down the leg side, and flicks the pad
driven hard to short midwicket, well fielded
defended on middle stump, solidly forward
a hint of turn as the ball straightens on middle. Solidly blocked again
no signs of discomfort there as Gul hits his length outside off, and Watson drives loosely
sliding into the pads, and flicked round the corner
solid line and length, defended back to the bowler
first signs of aggression from Haddin as he gave himself room for a slap, but his shot went straight to Misbah at short extra
a very cunning slower ball, wraps his fingers round the side, and the ball dribbles past a swish and through to Akmal on the fifth bounce
banged in short, a measured pull to backward square
driven with a closed face to mid-on
short, but skids through, defended from the crease
fuller length, met with a big stride
a compact drive to mid-off
probing work from Rehman, Watson is finding the middle well enough, but no width to work with
on the pads to finish, a grateful flick to midwicket
banged in short, a swivel pull through midwicket
full length and defended to cover
that's the nut! Bang on target, nip off the seam, a loose drive and a touch of inside edge, and the stumps are shattered!
tight line, and defended off the back foot
deflected to midwicket, hopping across the stumps a touch, as is his wont
outside off, Ponting shoulders arms dramatically
defended on off stump, out to midwicket
bonk. That was an up and under lofted drive, all timing and just enough power as the ball plops over the rope at long-on
defended into the off side
stands tall in defence, and works the ball to cover off an inside edge
big stride and blocked on off
aside from that one big blow, another tidy over from Rehman
on the pads, whisked into the leg side, without much timing
attacking off stump once again, Ponting's defences are tested again
a loopy slower ball, cunningly bowled but Ponting picked it early and defended
on the hip, flicked fine. Slim pickings so far against the wily Gul
another slower ball, and Ponting has to scamper for his ground as Haddin turns down a sharp single in the gully. That could have been tight
defended out to midwicket. Another unrelentingly accurate over from Gul
flicked out to square leg
Haddin advances, but Rehman's line is too good. Forced to defend
blocked from the crease this time. Good metronomic work
punched into the covers, but there's nothing doing there
poor ball, down the leg-side, and though it's a wide, Haddin missed out on an easy four as he swept at thin air
back on a better line
fenced out to point, and the grind continues for the Aussies
on the pads, flicked to square leg. No bat involved
advancing again, but still unable to thread the gap, Haddin's drive rolls to mid-off
slower ball, beautifully bowled, Ponting waits and dabs a single to mid-on
whoops. That was Gul's first show of aggression, and ropey as Akmal's keeping may be, he was never going to intercept that!
hits the seam and jags back in, but that was doing too much. Good delivery though
flicked round the corner again, to backward square
slower delivery, but too short, and Haddin's delayed pull has enough legs to go all the way. Australia needed that
round the wicket, looped onto a good length, defended
a hint of turn from middle stump. Straightens into a defensive push
punched to long-on
tossed up towards the blockhole, defended again
on the pads, poked to short midwicket
good areas, as they say. Pitching middle from wide on the crease, and straightening. Defended
a fraction short, and cut hard to point. Well stopped
tossed up, and driven compactly to cover
devious through the air, and zipping into a defensive push outside off
blocked solidly on off stump
the blade turns in the hands but midwicket tidies up. No angles for Australia to work with yet
pushed firmly to  cover. Pakistan in complete command at the moment. But they'll like a few wickets for their pressure
whippy delivery on off stump, Haddin jabs down into the gully and a sharp piece of fielding saves a run
short and pulled handsomely, off the front foot, but without a lot of power
a valuable boundary, and with fine leg up, Wahab can't really bowl there, on the hips. Enough bat to beat the field
on the pads again, Wahab's line isn't right just yet. A slide at square leg saves another four
probed into the gully
pushed down the track to mid-off. A bit of pressure released in that over
pushed into the gap to keep the strike rotating
belted, hard and straight. Not a lot of feet involved, not a lot needed. That fizzed onto the bat, and straight off again
flighted and defended on off stump. Good bounce in that topspinner
sharp calling for a deflection into the gully
Australia starting to pick up the tempo now, a few quick singles making themselves available through urgent calls and calm deflections
a flat-footed whoosh outside off stump. Half an appeal from Akmal
on the pads from Wahab, not quite the right line yet
that was a remarkable shot! Short, and badly beaten by sharp lift, and Ponting's late pull takes a fat top-edge and sails over the keeper's head for four!
another single to keep the strike rotating
that's a poor ball, Wahab is letting the noose slip now, with a wide down the leg side
punched through point
over-pitched outside off this time, and that's Ponting at his best. Leaning into his cover-drive and piercing the field. He's getting into his stride now
on the pads, turned through midwicket
carefully prodded back to the bowler
quick and flat, sliding into Haddin who hurriedly pushed to leg
once again Haddin is full of respect, which is no common thing
touch more air here, Afridi tempting up outside off stump. Haddin eases into a drive to cover
huge appeal from bowler and keeper as Afridi slides one into Ponting's pads but a big, big stride prevented trouble
more secure here for the batsman, full-facing a single down the ground
googly to finish the over, plenty of overspin finds some extra bounce. Haddin is unperturbed and nudges around the corner
tight line around middle on a length and Haddin content to push it away
very careful from Haddin again, tapping back to the bowler
hint of uncertainty as Haddin plays for spin that isn't there
prodded back to the bowler again, good run of dots being built
tossed up outside off stump, Haddin stretches across to dab back to Hafeez
finally the single is taken as Haddin's flick goes wide of the bowler down to long-on
no timing here for Haddin as he slaps to point
ooh, the pressure almost told there. Attempting to run down to third man came off the bottom edge, onto the boot, very close to the stumps and almost to the keeper
this time Haddin is more secure in defence
Afridi is really tossing this up, clearly feels in good control and Haddin threads a single into space
ah, nothing there for Ponting. He wanted to squeeze a cut away but it was too close to him for the shot
nothing as ambitious this time from Ponting, instead easing his hands over the ball to flick to leg
Misbah has dropped Ponting at square leg! Really hard sweep flew low to him and went straight through. Looked like a tough chance though
Haddin more calmly works a single
careful defence from Ponting, he hasn't looked safe against Hafeez at all

gone! Akmal has held a very good catch and Ponting has to go! Things really bubbling over here. Ponting went back to cut a ball which wasn't really there for it, got a thick edge that Akmal did well to hold. It was given not out originally, but rightly was overturned on review. While waiting for the third umpire to confirm the edge there was some verbal exchanges though between Haddin and the Pakistan fielders and plenty of chat as Ponting was sent on his way
bit of spin here for Hafeez back into Clarke who prods it to leg
carefully defended into the off side. Looked a touch uncertain as he did, getting a leading edge
starts a touch short and  down the leg side, nibbled away behind square
banged into the pitch short of a length. Haddin calmly stands tall to defend
looks like Haddin has set his stall out to bat through. Very watchful at the moment
much better this over from Wahab. This is his best delivery yet, good length around off stump, Haddin was hanging back and had to jab his defence away
too short this time and allows Haddin to turn a single to midwicket

Clarke gets four when he so nearly could have gone! Loose shot really, aiming an airy drive to a shortish ball, flew off the inside edge close to the stumps and actually not all that far from the wicketkeeper before disappearing to the boundary
Umar scoots around at midwicket to cut off a Haddin flick
doosra, or possibly just one that didn't spin. Either way Haddin was very careful in defence
ooh, Haddin advances and again is defeated by back of turn, thickish outside edge ran along the ground to point
this is far safer, pushed down to long-on
Clarke flicks firmly but straight to square leg
the bounce and sprightliness seems to have returned to Clarke's set up at the crease. Even as he defends back to the bowler
Haddin wants a pop at Wahab I suspect, he's edging down the crease and winding up for a big shot but doesn't get the width he wants so only pushes back to the bowler
this time there is width outside off and Haddin creams a drive to deep point
better delivery this time, back of a length around off stump. Blocked to cover
touch too wide and Clarke flashes a cut shot out to third man
nonsense down the leg side. Doesn't look like Wahab can land six deliveries consistently
that's more like it from Wahab, fuller, quicker and straighter. Earns a forward block for the effort
Haddin gets the slightest invitation of width and dabs down to third man
very delicate from Haddin opening the face to steer to third man. Fairly ineffective though because there is a fielder there
clipped past a diving Umar at midwicket, who is disgusted with himself for missing
good work from Hafeez pinning Clarke to the crease
Clarke whips to leg but picks out midwicket
ooh, flash and a miss outside off stump. Similar to the Ponting dismissal but Clarke is in form so misses. Such are the unwritten laws of the game
good work from Clarke here, skipping down the wicket and clipping to long-on
too short from Wahab means Clarke can stand tall and run down to third man
Haddin flashes outside off stump and misses
more secure this time by Haddin, getting in line to defend under his eyes

Wahab strikes and  Australia are in trouble now! Akmal takes another catch! I between the dross Wahab has found some bounce and nibble and Haddin aimed a nothing steer to third man, got a faint edge and Kamran held on to the chance.
after the good delivery Wahab serves up an easy one on the pads for White to clip towards square leg for a couple
this is fuller, much fuller but outside off stump and ignored by White
Hafeez is doing a fine, fine job here. Nothing fancy, just hitting lengths and lines and nowhere for Clarke to go
very carefully defended once more
ooh, this was a very tight single. Clarke picked out Misbah at midwicket and hared off for a single. A quicker pick-up and a direct hit would have gone but as it was Clarke was safe
White is hanging back in his crease and looks rushed as he blocks this
carefully defended once more this time White got forward though
ooh, doosra slides past a groping, flat-footed outside edge!
Wahab is pounding in after his wicket and this is quick but the length and line is wrong
the shot looks risky but really from this line - wide outside off - Clarke is safe. He flashed an expansive drive off a thickish edge that flew past the slip to the third-man boundary
poor shot this time, Wahab seems to have Clarke's beans going here. Just stood still and swiped across the line at fresh air
far calmer on this occasion with Clarke flagging one through outside off
Afridi fluffs a regulation stop at mid-off but it was always going to be a single
good run to bring up the Australia 100. White drops to point with soft hands and scoots through for a single
solid delivery to end the over, on a length at off stump and Clarke gives it the respect it deserves
nothing for White here as he pushes back to the bowler
White's hard hands unable to work the ball and he clunks to mid-on
again White is pinned to the crease as he pushes to leg
unable to work singles White aims an almighty hack, can't connect but the ball springs off the pads for a single
Clarke is all wrists and quick feet as he picks off a single to deep square
White again clunks back to the bowler. Excellent work from Hafeez again
starts well by tossing it up a little, Clarke pushes wide of the bowler is search of a single but Afridi scoots around
touch shorter and quicker and Clarke is back in a flash flicking into the leg side for a couple
Clarke is offered some width to drive at but is careful on the shot
this time he does pick up a single, flicking into space
good hands from White here, finally, as he nudges to deep square
hint of spin from a shortish length, Clarke waits and then drives his bottom hand through the ball to send it from outside off stump down to long-on
this keeps a little low, and Hafeez is nothing if not straight to Clarke defends
little bit short from the bowler and Clarke wheels away a pull shot
good follow-up, keeping the strike ticking by pushing down the ground
White can't match his partner's skills and picks out a fielder
big sweep heaved away this time, all along the ground to deep square
twinkle toes and quick wrists gets Clarke a single to long-on. When he plays well it's a treat watching Clarke play spin bowling
again Clarke skips down the wicket and flicks to midwicket
if Clarke is all wrists, White is all forearms and offered some width here bludgeons the ball down the ground
little bit too short and Clarke drags it to long-on
White tries to steal a single by dropping this towards point but he gets too much of it
in the end it looks a good shot but White would have been worried for a moment as he lifted this high down towards long off
carefully defended to finish the over
chaos! White is run out in a terrible mix-up, a flick off the hip, Misbah swooped at short backward square, Akmal takes and the replay is conclusive!
defended on the back foot
pushed into the covers and an urgent, typically urgent, single
Clarke returns the compliment
flicked off the toes to midwicket
Clarke steps back into the crease and pushes a single to mid-on
quicker delivery, strikes the thigh pad
a measured push to long-on
tapped out to cover, a good confident stride into the shot
"easy easy" is the call as Hussey cuts calmly to deep cover
full toss, but Clarke is too entrenched to take full toll. A push to long-on
one more scamper into the covers
round the wicket, and tucked off the hip
down the track but without much malice. Clipped to short midwicket
good use of the feet to cut hard down to third man, but more sharp work on the boundary's edge saves four
clipped uppishly through square leg. It's slow going out there
short and leg-sided. Hussey's ambitious smear doesn't come off as Akmal rushes round to field a deflection
a soft-handed dab to cover. One more to the total
tapped to cover
clipped down to long-on
open-faced steer to gully, but can't beat the field
driven out to midwicket
sits up a touch outside off, Hussey jabs through the gap at point
another single threaded up to long-off. Australia living off scraps at the moment, just one boundary since Haddin's departure
clear signs of a two-paced pitch there, the ball died on impact and Clarke pulled at thin air
defended with a hop into line, might have kept a bit low but Clarke hammed it up a touch
poked in the air, straight back past the bowler, who nearly brushes his fingers on the ball as it thuds into the non-striker's stumps
that was coming all the way through that over. Clarke didn't look happy at Razzaq's box of tricks, and an attempted pull somehow wriggles through the stroke to dislodge the off bail
a hard-handed poke outside off, the slip was there but he couldn't get close, though third man tidies up
an eventful introduction from the evergreen Razzaq. How long has he been around now?
pushed to midwicket, where Misbah again flings himself as if he's in the first flush of youth
on the pads, flicked to midwicket
Hussey uses his feet, and eludes the diving Misbah at short midwicket
tip and run from Smith, who finds space at point and scampers through
good aggression from the Pakistanis, a quick pick-up at short midwicket and a sharp shy to keep the non-striker honest
bounce from nowhere for Razzaq. Smith removes one hand from the handle to ride the lift on that one
forward cautiously and defended
excellent work once again from Pakistan. A quick pick-up at mid-on, and the shy  from Younis hits the stumps. Not much excitement though, as Smith is well home
beaten! That cut straight through Hussey, who was lucky not to inside-edge onto his own stumps
drilled hard, more of a square drive than a cut, but point pouched it in an instant. Pakistan are so alert today!
bashed down to long-on, another single to end another tight over
chiselled from outside off to midwicket. Another single
tucked down to long on
reverse sweep, doesn't connect

that's as soft as a baby possum. Hussey hardly got to the pitch of that one, and lobbed a simple chance to short midwicket. The two-paced wicket might take some of the blame, but that was poor from such an experienced campaigner
solidly forward, and defended to cover
subtle turn from outside the left-hander's off stump. Blocked solidly
short, and spanked, up and over midwicket, but without much timing. Plops into no-man's land at cow corner
solidly forward, and defended
back of a length but targeting off. Driven with that peculiar hard-handed style down to third man
outside off, nipping off the seam, grazing the edge, and Johnson is gone for a duck! The extra bounce did the trick, and Akmal's glovework has been as good as ... well, ever, probably
attempted yorker, good thinking, but drifting a touch down the leg-side. Steered to midwicket
clear signs of reverse swing as Razzaq is really tearing in now. Defended solidly enough on off stump
tapped into space to keep the score rolling
poked to cover from deep in the crease
defended back down the track
that beat everything, Akmal included. Missed stumping? Perhaps. Akmal's day had been too good to last
blocked out to point, and the Aussie struggle continues
Smith is Australia's only hope. Imagine that. Pushed out to cover
Razzaq finding some kind of indrift and Smith pokes to midwicket
final 10 overs and Smith has to be very watchful and respectful in defence
steered down to third man, Smith seems so pleased with the shot he held the pose. With a technique as ugly as his that's a brave move
Krejza stabs down on a straight ball
Razzaq doing nothing more tricky than holding a line outside off stump. Where as this against Ross Taylor? Anyway, Krejza defends
ooh, Smith gets in a woeful tangle top-edging an attempted dip over the keeper. It looped probably 10 metres behind Kamran but he had no interest in going for it. Still, he's held a few today
pushed away securely for a single
Smith gets forward and defends with something approaching orthodoxy
Smith down on one knee and this time manages to dink his sweep more effectively which, combined with smart running earns him a couple
carefully nudged to midwicket to bring Krejza, who has a first-class ton, on strike
toe-ended cut shot runs out to deep cover.
already some reverse swing, dipping into the batsman at 146kph. Some horrid stick-a-foot-out-and-hope fielding from Afridi gifts a single. He then stretches to take everyone's mind off what happens
no swing from this length, hammered short and Smith jumps tall to drop by his feet and scoot for one
slip in place for Krejza but Gul admonishes himself for shoving down a short and wide one. Krejza is equally annoyed for missing it
this is a better ball, though curiously back of a length again. Krejza drops it to cover to exchange a single with Smith
wow, this ferociously good timing this. Offered width Smith somehow ended up in a very conventional position to drive and it flew through the covers
strange, only one yorker from that Gul over. This is a length delivery again and steered to third man
Afridi brings himself back into the attack  and almost squeezes through the defence but it bobbles off an edge
this is held back a touch and pushed into space
carefully worked away, much quicker delivery
dragged down a touch short and cut firmly out to deep point
Smith ambles up the wicket and aims a whip to leg. Defeated by a touch of spin
slower from Afridi, Smith guides to short third man
much too short and much too wide, this is poor stuff from Gul and Australia just building a decent run of play here. Krejza cuts out in front of deep cover for a couple
better, much better. More intent on this Gul delivery, firing it in fuller and sliding into Smith who couldn't work it away
there it is! The Umar Gul inswinging yorker strikes again. Why did he wait so long? Krejza backed away to give himself room to pierce the off side but he missed and the stumps were shattered instead
ooh, a second slip would have had it. As it is the outside edge flew wide of first slip and skimmed to the ropes. 200 must be Australia's target
hooping, late reverse-swing at a full length would have burst through but for Lee's inside edge
this one nips away and past an enquiring outside edge. Much better over from Gul that
the field comes in and Smith picks out cover
prodded back to the bowler
little bit short but it's quickly onto the batsman who flips a single towards midwicket
speared a long way down the leg side
googly finds the gloves as Lee defends with very low hands, there are no slips in place or catchers up to the crease so Lee can feel safe
Afridi strikes! Smith backs away to a googly that follows him and it crashes into middle stump
full, flat, spearing yorker. Tait manages to jab a bat down
this isn't a yorker but it's quick on a length, moving away and carefully blocked to cover
that's the delivery that he's famed for! It snakes back so late homing in on the toes. Lee desperately clamps a bat down in time
yorker followed by a short ball followed by a stare! Excellent bowling, this climbed past Lee
that's it! Australia slump to 176 all out - their lowest since 1992. Pakistan have a celebratory huddle! Lee aimed a swipe but it got high on the bat and looped to mid-off

inn2.comm: a beauty to start the innings, perfect line and length, and a nibble of late swing. Akmal swishes at thin air
more swing under the floodlights, and that one doesn't get up either. Left alone, but already signs of that uneven bounce
blocked on off stump, no swing this time as Akmal defends with an open face
that's a hideous stroke, but they all count. An ugly cross-batted wave of the bat, more of a standing sweep than a full-blooded pull. A big top edge and none of the slips can get close!
a mix-up in the middle of the pitch! Kamran flicks off his hip, and the batsmen almost shake hands while deciding whether to run. The shy goes wide
stands firm in defence. A lively start!
a big effort, and a decent line. Outside off, through to the keeper
you can't bowl there to an opener! On the toes, flicked beautifully through square leg. No stopping that one
extra lift from a good length, strong wrists turn a single to fine leg
three slips in place now as Akmal fences a single to third man
a swish and a miss, outside off, swinging late towards the slips. Good delivery
that's the worst of Tait shortly after the best of him. An ugly bouncer, barely crosses the tramlines
and now he tightens his line again. Sharp
banged into the hip, flicked to square leg
excellent carry from a tight line. Well left
full and straight,  not quite a yorker, but attacking the stumps. Pushed to mid-off

there it is! The breakthrough looked imminent, and so it was. A rapid delivery, Hafeez closed the face too early as he attempted to work a straight ball through midwicket, but a looping leading edge tempts Lee into a full-on sprint out of his follow-through, and he clings on to an excellent stretching take!
fast and full, strikes the pad but sliding down leg
a hint of width and slashed greedily through the vacant gully. Third man collects on the bounce. This is gripping viewing
poor work from the skipper in the covers. A rare miss as Pakistan tipped and ran, and they were able to get back for two as his damaged left hand lets him down
fast again, and defended
a down-on-one-knee pile-drive of a stroke, but the ball is already in the keeper's gloves
full and a fraction of swing, and that's tapped in front of square on the leg side
short, outside off, but that one dies on impact.
sumptuous from Shafiq, Tait's line wasn't all that bad, but the shot was timed to perfection from middle-and-leg, and no-one can intercept on the leg-side boundary!
full, fast, swinging, hits the pads, a big appeal but Lee is late to join in. That was missing leg, and they don't bother to review
this one holds its line on off stump and is pumped back to the bowler, who threatens to shy
driven again, into the covers
blocked on off stump, keeps a touch low, but Akmal gets the full face behind the line

humungous appeal, and Ponting has gone for the review! Definitely closer than the last appeal, but it might remain an umpire's call. Hit deep in the crease but swinging, and that has clipped leg. Sure enough, it's not out
straight as a die, back of a length, defended cautiously back to the bowler. Lee is bowling his socks off here
good start from Johnson but an excellent early call to a soft-handed block
too much width and that's slapped hard through the covers. You can't bowl there etc ...
much better line, tight to off stump and threatening to swing back into the pads. Poked to point
banged in short, Akmal ducks
signs of swing, but it merely swings straight into the middle of Akmal's bat! Too much width again, and this is an expensive over in the context of a tight contest
better line, defended uneasily. A welcome over for Pakistan
on the pads, deflected to short fine leg
tight line, shaping from leg-and-middle towards off. Defended on the walk, back to the bowler
short and defended on the hop, back to the bowler
chopped down to third man
too full and clipped firmly to backward square
driven out to cover, some of the menace was lacking in that Lee over.
edged ... but good soft hands ensure that the ball dies long before it reaches first slip
good from Johnson, lift off a good length, and defended out to point
full, and driven up to mid-off. Not much sign of swing yet for Mitch
outside off, left well alone
firmly forward and driven into the covers. A composed stroke for no run
too straight, tapped with a roll of the wrists through midwicket, where Tait can't pounce. A quick outfield and excellent timing. Mitch isn't happy
misdirected, and worked superbly past short fine leg, but what's happened to Shafiq?
a big inside-edge saves Akmal from a raucous lbw appeal! Full, fast and straight
clobbered! Too short and wide, and Akmal loves the cut shot. That fizzed

there it is! A big appeal, late in-dip from a full length, but Akmal has gone for the review. I think it's optimistic. He was struck on the back leg, and that will surely clip the stumps. Indeed it does. A vital breakthrough!
lift on off stump, and defended to cover
sturdy defence on an off-stump line. The end of an incisive over. Can Australia find a man to back up Lee's efforts?
full, but no swing. Pushed to cover
outside off, whistling through, left alone
a loose slash, that was a touch rash, though not the best ball Johnson has bowled. Too much width
slower ball, defended from the crease
crunched into the covers, can't pierce the field
blocked solidly on off stump
starts with a creaky loosener on the pads but it's only nudged away
slip in place and rightly so, Watson finds some away-movement. Younis steers  to point and hurries off for a single that was probably a little tighter then he expected
awful delivery, full and filthy down the leg side. Shafiq only had to tickle, and tickle he did
much better delivery, not hard to be I suppose, Shafiq blocks
another gimme served up on the pads, flicked away to deep square
Watson finds something close to off stump but Younis seemed to have an age to ease forward and defend
Johnson is full and on middle, clipped around the corner
oh dear, the pitch has quietened down but Pakistan's running is a shambles here. Dabbed to Hussey at point and a suicidal single would have been out with a direct hit
very neatly flicked off around middle to deep square. None of the other Aussie seamers have found the fire that Lee did
better delivery outside off stump and left alone
ooh, Younis would call it a steer, Johnson an edge. Either way it went past slip to third man  to the annoyance of Johnson
solid defence to end the over
Watson continues and continues badly. On the pads again at a gentle pace and Younis helps himself to a single at midwicket
bouncer banged in, big effort ball but crept up to Shafiq who swatted down to deep midwicket
better delivery here, full and straight and defended
Watson locates a good length and line again. Younis rewards him with defence
ah, bit of movement in the air. Swing of some description. Younis is again respectful in defence
very full and a touch of swing into the batsman. Driven to mid-on. Tidy end to the over but wickets are the only currency that counts with such a modest total to defend
grunts down a short and wide ball. It looked too short and too wide but the umpire let him be
he doesn't quite look at full throttle but the swing keeps the batsman honest. Which is a virtue
very fluid looking drive but it for no reward
good delivery this time, full and shaping into Shafiq who defends in a hurry
again the movement into the batsman causes trouble. Shafiq inside edging back to the bowler
full and fast. Blocked back to the bowler
starts very straight, looks like he's warmed into his task. Younis blocks back to him
hint of inswing but the line remains impeccable
nicely done from Younis, opening the face to send this down to third man
Watson is definitely finding inswing but at a very gentle pace and easily pushed to mid-on
this time the length is too short, the line too far down leg and it's clipped to deep square as a result
looked like Watson was attempting a bouncer, which at his pace is a touch ambitious. After waiting a while for the ball to arrive, it's wheeled to deep square
fired down the leg side
this is straighter and Younis solidly defends
plenty of effort from Tait but without much reward. Even the pace is only 88mph. Younis has a while to get into line and defend
the placement was better than the timing on this drive. Shafiq insisted on haring back for a third which looked dicey because he slipped  as he turned but still makes it in time
full on the pads and Shafiq flicks with the angle to deep square
low full toss fired in and Younis bullets a drive back from where it came from. It can be difficult to time those but it raced to the fence
solid defence ends another over. The strike bowler just can't strike. Looks down on pace and a touch tired
not sure how Watson is going to make this breakthrough. These two look very solid against him
Shafiq eases a drive to cover without much timing
Ponting is fielding at silly mid-on. He collects a mistimed drive and pings back a throw at Haddin
looked like a slower ball, they are all fairly slow though. The line is wrong and it's tucked off the pads
very little pace of bounce in either the wicket or bowler. Driven to point
Watson looks to the heavens in disbelief that Younis should have middled a forward defence
finds big spin first up, bit of bounce too and cramped Shafiq's cut
big forward lunge outside off in response to smother the spin
this delivery landed in the same place as the first but didn't turn at all. Variation?
ooh, Shafiq leapt down the track and just turned his bat too early getting a leading edge to mid-off. Fair to say the spinner should have been one earlier
Younis flows a drive to fall ball, really tried to smack it, but no timing
ooh, short leg would have had it. As it is it bobbles off the gloves into space but an excellent start from Krejza
edged! But only for four, this proud record is slipping away for Australia! Wide of off, Shafiq aimed an expansive drive but it flew off the edge to take the target to 100
solid and sturdy defence to a full ball

again Shafiq is solidly forward. Ponting and Watson have some sort of discussion over where the catcher should be, didn't look particularly agreeable actually but Ponting has moved out of silly mid-on and posted a slip
another careful defence. After chancing his arm first ball, Shafiq is not going to again
bottom-handed flip towards midwicket earns a single
Watson should be grateful Clarke dived full-length at point to brush a hand on this or it would have been four. Dished up full and wide, Younis crashed a drive
full toss and Younis take full toll. Driven back down the ground and Johnson made no real effort to catch up from long-on
this time it's defended carefully
tossed up again outside off, Younis stretches across to defend
this pops off the glove into space where short leg could have been. Krejza asks his captain to post a man there, Australia need wickets in a hurry but still no short leg in place
plenty of flight and Younis is again stretching into line but this time to flash a drive to deep point
sharp spin from outside off is defended
full length, a touch of inswing, drilled hard to cover
streaky from Younis, it was a good ball and a loose stroke. I think it was an intentional dab through the cordon, but it flew uncomfortably close to Haddin. And the slip had only just been moved!
cautiously forward to defend
poked out to point
now that is a shot. The stroke of the day, a full and handsome drive through the covers. A bit of width, but what a majestic strike!
dabbed down to the gully, and that was a valuable over for Pakistan's cause
two steps, and flicked to midwicket
crease-bound this time, and wafted to midwicket again
attacking line outside off, and always threatening to turn and bounce. Prodded in front of square on the leg side
an excellent shot, tossed up outside off, and confidently swept to deep square leg
short but spinning, cut fiercely out to deep cover
tossed up, and driven to cover. Good over, but the runs continue to come
banged in short but straight, fenced down to third man
back of a length again, defended to cover
flicked from a leg-stump line, another single to the cause
the change works! Younis has played a ropey dab outside off stump, a thin but undoubtable nick through to Haddin, and Australia have their opening!
two in two! Sensational bowling from Lee! Outside off, in the channel, just enough lift, and Misbah's loose poke finds a grazed edge to Haddin!
good ball but not enough for the hat-trick, attacking the stumps, and Umar defends from deep in the crease
down on the sweep, and paddled square
looped up, and driven hard to cover
splatted out to cow corner, an agriculturally elegant slog-sweep. Somehow it went along the ground all the way ...
more orthodox this time
down the leg side, but no wide called
delicately dabbed round the corner, the sweep comes into play again
full and straight again, defended
attempted yorker comes out as a low full toss, punched to cover for an instant single
attacking length once again, but Umar still had a lot of time to play his drive.
battered! What a strike! Down on one knee, smeared on the up and through the covers! Fetch that
whisked in the air through backward square. Umar wants to get this requirement gobbled up in a hurry, and it's probably not a bad policy
Lee pulls his length back for a decent rib-tickler, but a loose shy gifts Pakistan an overthrow - in fact it was Lee's errant boot which blasted the ball past the stumps!
outside off, swinging late, a missed back-cut
more swing for Johnson, and a limp poke outside off
squeezed off the pads, in front of square. Two more valuable runs
outside off, left alone
more width, and Umar reaches for that, and finds the middle of the bat. In the air, but clears the ring ...
on the pads, clipped fine. Fine leg tidies up
good running, a turn of the wrists and a quick call to short midwicket. Shafiq keeps the strike
short, but unthreatening. That's his one for the over
short again, outside off, dabbed off an under-edge out to gully. A sharp single brings Umar on strike, and the crowd shuffles forward in its seats ...
leg-stump line, not offering any room to swing the arms. Clipped to midwicket
humungous wind-up to a delivery that was fractionally outside off! That could have whizzed through midwicket. Instead it inside-edged onto his pads
stands tall, and drives hard to cover
low full toss, drilled into the gap at midwicket, Umar keeps the strike
solid defence on the line of off stump. That was almost as exaggerated as Andrew Flintoff's leather-sniffing block
a teaser outside off, Umar has a thrash. And misses
glided down to third man, just enough width to work with
excellent delivery, outside off, holds its line and bursts past the edge
this is an excellent over, Johnson's left-arm angle is cramping the Pakistanis' ambitions outside off
edged but safe, down to third man
short, and that was ambitiously pulled, up and over midwicket. He needed a stepladder to play it comfortably, but fortune favoured the brave
solid defence, right behind the line
squeezed to cover
big stride, solid defence. None shall pass
a whistling bouncer, good decision to duck that one!
a crashing cut, straight to Clarke at point. Well intercepted, because that was travelling
that's how Umar plays! One step down the track and walloped up and over cow corner!
outside off, and an almost comical leave-alone, given the flamboyance of the previous stroke
outside off again
flicked fine, square leg gathers
elegant drive, straight to cover
good delivery to finish, climbing towards off, and defended
toss it up outside off, that's what. Somehow Umar resists all his most base temptation and blocks
big spin here, starts outside off ends outside leg
didn't take Umar long! Sees the flight, dances down and hammers it up and over long-on for a  maximum
now back to cautious defence, he's actually played this innings superbly
tickled around the corner to exchange the strike
Shafiq has played like a World Cup veteran in his second World Cup game
the only thing that has troubled Umar has been half-volleys and short balls from Johnson, oddly. This is short and wide but he fresh-airs a swish
having reasoned he can't seem to play without missing outside off Umar decides he won't play at all
dropped into the leg side, huge cry of "nooo" from the batsman. It's been one of the rare innings where Umar has used his brains, today. And he looks indecently gifted when he does
calmly driven, but straight to cover
couple of skips down the track but when he didn't get the half-volley he wanted Umar just nudged a single square of the wicket. That shot alone demonstrates how clearly he's thinking

a twist!? Surely not. But it is Pakistan, they're like England! Johnson removes the anchor Shafiq. Extra bounce clips the glove and heads towards slip, Haddin sprawls across to confuse the catcher but Watson's composure is intact and so it the catch!
Krejza offers plenty of air to Umar but nothing silly attempted, that's the captain's job. Single nudged to midwicket
the crowd are heaving, expecting some Boom Boom. Instead Afridi pops forward and Boycotts a defence
oh dear, Afridi is more sensible than the Australian fielders here. Carefully steers a single before Johnson overthrows to make it two
ooh, hint of leading edge sends it back to the bowler

well, that was woefully predictable. Wearily predictable. Block, block, block, bust! Skips down the wicket, leans back and heaves. Not sure he bothered looking at the ball though and it went straight down long-on's throat
huge spin from outside off but Umar watches it carefully and keeps the strike by dabbing a single to midwicket
Johnson around the wicket to Umar, lands it outside off and Umar flags it through
picked off the hip to square leg
oh, inside edge to the rescue. Just. Razzaq hanging deep in his crease to a pitched-up inswinger. Dreadful shot really, deserved to be out but somehow landed a faint inside edge down to fine leg
slower ball that Umar spots and steers past point, there's a bit of mix-up between the batsmen but eventually they cross for a single
Razzaq has abandoned foot movement to play Johnson and looks all the more shaky for it. Dabbed without any conviction to midwicket
Umar solidly behind this
Krejza floats one up outside off and Razzaq steps confidently into a drive. Looks happier away from the pace
dragged down short and despite a lot of turn Umar waits, picks a gap and powerfully cuts for four. The cut to the spinners can be dangerous but Umar played it superbly
follows the boundary with a well-timed drive for a single. Pakistan fans will be breathing a little easier now
Razzaq pops forward to defend
Razzaq resists the temptation to swipe across the line and instead reaches for the textbook to drive a single to deep cover
smart and sturdy defence from Umar
goodness, this pitches and dies though to Haddin
absolutely nothing here for Tait, it's like he's bowling into a sandpit. Razzaq wants to be terrified - hanging back desperately - but the ball takes an age to reach him
ooh, Umar just rushed for pace here. Somehow Tait generated some life and a top-edged hook looped one-bounce to midwicket
having diced with death Umar reverts to discipline and leaves alone outside off
banged in short again, this time Umar gets up on his toes to deftly block it to point
not sure he needed to try this, stepping outside off to hack to leg. Ended up bottom-edging and it trickles away
much too short from  Krejza but Razzaq misses out on the gift
wow, sharp, biting spin from outside off bursts through the gate to trap Razzaq on the pads. Big appeal but it was going over
worked with the spin into the leg side
tossed up and Umar stretches forward to defend
flash and a miss outside off! Umar just losing concentration as the target nears
worked to leg this time, much safer. Umar has done so well to get this far, just needs to work the singles now
Tait and his off-colour day continues, full on the pads, Razzaq tickles a couple and the target is under 20 now!
18 to go as Tait slings a wide one outside off
this time Tait lands a quick one, sliding past the edge through to Razzaq
poor old Tait, he's busting his body to drag something out of the old ball and tired pitch but the short ball gets barely shin high
looked like an edge here! Fell just short of Haddin who fumbled the take to allow Razzaq through
Tait lands a rapid yorker that Umar neatly, thoughtfully even, guides to third man for a well-run couple
flash and miss outside off! To be fair to Umar it was there to hit but for some reason he missed it
ooh, bottom-edge lands close to the stumps but Razzaq survives
better this time, guiding the ball with a straight bat to cover
Umar whips his bottom hand through the ball with the spin but picks out midwicket
flicked firmly down the ground for a riskless single
Razzaq is attempting another cut and without quite timing it earns a single to cover
the turn and bounce beats everyone, including Haddin. Just jumped from a length and Haddin couldn't collect cleanly
ooh, already he's found something that Tait couldn't. It zips off the track and climbs past Razzaq's outside edge
good line from Lee, around off stump. Razzaq drives loosely but without alarm
smoothly driven through cover. Nine needed now and finally the heads are dropping. Ponting has been stroppy all tournament and looks thoroughly annoyed at the moment
slower ball, or at least the pitch made it a slower ball. Umar waits, nudes to leg and jogs through
still more hostility from Lee! Bangs in a short ball that climbs past Razzaq and crashes into Haddin's gloves
full-pitched to finish the over. Very straight too, but so was Razzaq's bat
finds really huge spin from a long way outside off, caught Umar by surprise but the batsman adjusted nicely to dab to point
driven off the back foot with the spin to mid-on
tossed up outside off but Umar's drive is careful
open-faced steer to point gives Umar a single and takes Pakistan even closer
just one hit away now! Too short from  Krejza and Razzaq gets deep into his crease to haul this through midwicket for four

that's it! Australia's proud undefeated run in World Cups finally comes to an end. Razzaq creams this through cover, calmly tucks his bat under his arm and walks off! Comfortable win in the end and Pakistan top the group!
